    <h2  ><a name="CVision"></a><span class="t-type">Cours</span> <span class="t-title">Vision Industrielle  </span> <span class="t-year">(4&egrave;me ann&eacute;e)</span></h2>
    <ul>
	  <li>Chapter 1: <strong>Introduction</strong>: Motivation, human vision, history, digital images, methodology</li>
      <li>Chapter 2: <strong>Image Acquisition</strong>: Image formation, sensors, cameras, scanners, illumination, color</li>
      <li>Chapter 3: <strong>The Fourier Transform</strong>: Noise, Fourier transformation, image filtering in the frequency domain, correlation [<a href="vision/download/vision_03_fourier_en.pdf">PDF</a>]</li>
      <li>Chapter 4: <strong>Image Processing</strong>: Linear and non linear filtering, histograms [<a href="vision/download/vision_04_filter_en.pdf">PDF</a>]</li>
      <li>Chapter 5: <strong>Image Analysis:</strong> Thresholding, gradients, laplacian, edge detection, region segmentation [<a href="vision/download/vision_05_analysis_en.pdf">PDF</a>]</li>
      <li>Chapter 6: <strong>Mathematical Morphology &amp; 3D</strong>: Binary images, erosion, dilation, opening, closing, neighborhood transformations, skeleton, thinning, Shape from X [<a href="vision/download/vision_06_morpho_en.pdf">PDF</a>]</li>
    </ul>
	
    <ul>
      <li>Sujet de l'examen 2003/2004: <a href="vision/download/intero20032004.pdf">[PDF</a>]</li>
      <li>Sujet de l'examen 2002/2003: <a href="vision/download/intero20022003.pdf">[PDF]</a></li>
    </ul>
    <ul>
      <li>Note: The PDF files have been optimized for printing, so they have been exported in gray levels instead of color (let's use a computer vision term since we are here to learn vision). Hint: the graphical complexity of the slides is quite high, so sometimes it is a good idea to set the printing options to "Level 1" if you have a postscript printer in order to obtain good results (or any results at all).</li>
    </ul>
	
    <h2><a name="TPVision"></a><span class="t-type">TP</span> <span class="t-title">Vision Industrielle</span> <span class="t-year">(4&egrave;me ann&eacute;e)</span></h2>
    <ul>
	  <li>Exemples: filtrage, seuillage, s&eacute;gmentation, morphologie math&eacute;matique (Web: <a href="http://telesun.insa-lyon.fr">telesun</a>) </li>
